                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 182/52</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State Concerning Subjects Still
                        To Be Settled by the Conference</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[Undated—<placeName>Circa</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-01">July 1,
                        1919</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prepare Hungarian and Bulgarian Treaties at once.</p>
                <p>Agree on boundaries of states with Russia and announce decisions.</p>
                <p>Postpone Turkish matters until German treaty is ratified and our Syrian
                        Commission<note n="62" xml:id="d276fn62">The King–Crane Commission.</note>
                    reports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
